textAfterTable: Holidays in Dahab Hotels in Dahab Flights to Dahab Weather Widgets Averages for Dahab in March March in Dahab sees the average temperatures climb, but not excessively so, daytime temperatures typically reach a maximum of 25 degrees, while early morning temperatures fall to 16 degrees. Sea temperatures reach their lowest values during February and March, but still hold up at a relatively warm 21 degrees. There are only two days with rainfall during an average March, with a monthly average of 3mm, although on the rare occasions when it does rain, heavy storms are possible. March is usually sunny with a daily average of 11 hours of bright sunshine. Windsurfing is a popular pastime in Dahab during the winter half-year. The Swiss Inn Resort is a good place to go for windsurfing activities at the nearby coastline, and the Resort organises jeep safari trips to various spots for diving including the notorious Blue Hole. Accommodation and sports and leisure facilities are available on-site. For those seeking relatively cheap (but still high-quality) accommodation, the Mercure Dahab Bay View Hotel is located nearby.
